Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.02,0:00:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The text and comment in today’s \NExamining the Scriptures Daily \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.06,0:00:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,was taken from a \NWatchtower study article with the theme \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.29,0:00:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“How Can We Maintain ‘a Waiting Attitude’?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.70,0:00:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s a timely question \Nfor all of us to ponder \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.80,0:00:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,because as that Watchtower said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.90,0:00:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“Impatience can be dangerous, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.70,0:00:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,for it can cause us to behave rashly.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.67,0:00:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s the antidote to impatience? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.04,0:00:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Open, please, \Nyour Bible to the theme text \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.24,0:00:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,for that Watchtower study \Nat Micah 7:7, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.68,0:00:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and let’s read Micah 7:7 together \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.99,0:00:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and consider for a few moments \Nhow Micah’s good example \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.46,0:00:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,can help us to maintain a waiting attitude. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.59,0:00:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That text reads: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.96,0:00:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“But as for me, \NI will keep on the lookout for Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.73,0:00:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I will show a waiting attitude.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.00,0:00:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Or as the footnote says: \N“I will wait patiently \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.01,0:00:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“for the God of my salvation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.27,0:01:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,My God will hear me.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.01,0:01:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s beautiful \Nthat in just that one verse, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.68,0:01:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,three times Micah refers \Nto his God—our God—Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.28,0:01:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And that’s a nice reminder \Nthat no matter what the situation is \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.55,0:01:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that may cause us to have feelings \Nof impatience or frustration, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.53,0:01:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,whenever we put a problem \Nor difficulty side by side \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.63,0:01:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,with our God, Jehovah, \Nwhat happens to the situation? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.07,0:01:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It appears smaller\N—manageable with his help. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.51,0:01:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We might conclude, as did Brother Karl Klein \Nas published in his life story, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.11,0:01:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that ‘if Jehovah permits it, \Nwe can take it.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.28,0:01:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,With Jehovah’s help, we can patiently endure \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.95,0:01:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,any trial, circumstance, or situation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.69,0:01:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,as long as necessary without losing our joy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.43,0:01:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Micah was confident of that.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.69,0:01:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Look again at chapter 7 and verse 7. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.73,0:01:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,By saying that he would \N“keep on the lookout for Jehovah,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.67,0:02:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,in effect, Micah was saying \Nthat he was determined\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.41,0:02:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to become like \Nan active sentry on a watchtower. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.98,0:02:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So let’s try to picture that: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.08,0:02:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,A wide-eyed watchman on high alert. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.25,0:02:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That was Micah, spiritually speaking. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.65,0:02:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,He was determined not to get impatient \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.02,0:02:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and not to get frustrated \Nwith things that he could not change. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.19,0:02:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it easy for Micah \Nto maintain a waiting attitude? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.10,0:02:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably not. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.10,0:02:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice the context that reveals \Nwhat circumstances were like \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.47,0:02:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,in Israel and in Judah \Nin Micah’s time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.91,0:02:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice as you consider \Nsome of the thoughts there \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.01,0:02:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,beginning in verse 2 \Nof Micah chapter 7. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.11,0:02:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,He says: “The loyal one \Nhas perished from the earth.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.52,0:02:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 3: “Their hands \Nare expert at doing what is bad.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.42,0:02:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 4: “Their best one is like thorns, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.69,0:03:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,their most upright one \Nis worse than a thorn hedge.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.87,0:03:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, in verse 5, he says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.87,0:03:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do not put faith in your companion \Nor trust a close friend. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.34,0:03:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Guard what you say to the one \Nwho lies in your embrace.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.74,0:03:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 6: “For a son despises his father, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.41,0:03:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“a daughter rises up against her mother, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.95,0:03:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“and a daughter-in-law \Nis against her mother-in-law; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.95,0:03:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,a man’s enemies \Nare the men of his household.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.75,0:03:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, times were difficult \Nwhen Micah was alive. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.96,0:03:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,During wicked King Ahaz’ rule, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.39,0:03:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the spiritual and moral conditions in Israel \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.83,0:03:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,deteriorated to an appalling state.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.83,0:03:39.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you relate to Micah’s circumstances? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.90,0:03:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,All of Jehovah’s people today \Nexperience a test of endurance, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.67,0:03:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,a test of patience, \Nbecause we’re living in a selfish world \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.38,0:03:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,where, according to the Scriptures,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.38,0:03:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,people are “unthankful, disloyal,” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.75,0:03:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,they have “no natural affection.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.85,0:03:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,True Christians are \N“objects of hatred,” as Jesus foretold. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.82,0:04:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of our brothers \Nand sisters experience \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.99,0:04:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,hatred and opposition \Nat school and at work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.79,0:04:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,nearly every day. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.63,0:04:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes that hatred \Nis within the family, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.57,0:04:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,from unbelieving family members.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.80,0:04:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Think, too, about the hatred \Nthat our brothers and sisters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.77,0:04:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,have experienced who are imprisoned. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.84,0:04:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I can’t help but think \Nabout the two sisters in Azerbaijan, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.68,0:04:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,who we’re praying fervently for \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.95,0:04:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,because of their unjust persecution, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.02,0:04:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,or 600 more in Eritrea, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.42,0:04:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Nagorno-Karabakh, Singapore, \NSouth Korea, and Turkmenistan. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.19,0:04:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are injustices \Nthat we long to see corrected. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.00,0:04:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We’d love to see \Nthose situations changed today! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.54,0:04:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But are we impatient? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.67,0:04:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No. \NWe cultivate a waiting attitude.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.84,0:04:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Added to these circumstances \Nare the health problems \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.78,0:04:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,that many of our brothers \Nand sisters are facing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.41,0:05:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,These too are tests of patience, \Ntests of endurance. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.55,0:05:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you’re dealing with a health challenge \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.89,0:05:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,or a family member or a friend of yours \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.92,0:05:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is battling one of these \Nto a greater or lesser degree. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.09,0:05:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It made me think of the broadcast \Nfor this month, for December, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.56,0:05:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,where we met \NSabina Hernandez, in Panama, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.63,0:05:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,who was born with a severe handicap.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.57,0:05:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Since birth, her life \Nhas been anything but normal. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.61,0:05:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But what an encouragement she is! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.01,0:05:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,She’s come to trust in Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.01,0:05:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Like Micah, \Nshe’s developed a waiting attitude, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.95,0:05:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and this sister is doing her best \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.62,0:05:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to serve Jehovah \Ndespite her health challenge. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.75,0:05:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,She looks forward to the day \Nwhen those circumstances will change, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.29,0:05:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and we do too. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.32,0:05:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We’d love to see it today, wouldn’t we?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.49,0:05:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, those problems will end, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.26,0:05:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and likely it will happen \Nsooner than we think. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.77,0:05:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But whether the end of our circumstances \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.00,0:05:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that are so difficult \Ncomes today or a little later, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.71,0:06:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,what can Micah’s example teach us? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.21,0:06:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, think a little deeper about Micah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.61,0:06:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Micah served faithfully \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.65,0:06:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,for some six decades, \Nsome sixty years. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.18,0:06:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He did live to see the fulfillment of some \Nof Jehovah’s judgement messages. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.36,0:06:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He did see some good fruitage \Nfrom his prophesying activity. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.29,0:06:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But did Micah live to see the fulfillment \Nof all of Jehovah’s promises? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.40,0:06:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.40,0:06:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what helped him to wait patiently, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.57,0:06:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to keep active, \Nto be confident in Jehovah? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.80,0:06:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It was his absolute confidence \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.87,0:06:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah would in time \Nfulfill all of His promises. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.94,0:06:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He trusted completely in Him.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.61,0:06:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, by way of a reminder, \Nwhat two practical steps \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.18,0:06:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,could we do or do more fully \Nthat will help us to cultivate \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.05,0:06:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that same trusting, \Nconfident waiting attitude?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.56,0:06:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The first is the text found \Nat 1 Thessalonians 5:17; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.67,0:06:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s read that together, \N1 Thessalonians 5:17. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.57,0:07:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you have it memorized. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.57,0:07:05.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s one of the easiest verses to do that\N—two words. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.04,0:07:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it tell us to do? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.04,0:07:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“Pray constantly.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.68,0:07:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to remember that prayer \Nis real communication with God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.55,0:07:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We can never be charged \Nwith talking too much to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.22,0:07:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,When it comes \Nto real communication with God, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.26,0:07:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,The Watchtower cited this text and said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.43,0:07:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“He is willing to listen endlessly \Nto those who do his will.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.23,0:07:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s accept that invitation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.23,0:07:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s pray constantly\Nabout the things that distress us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.14,0:07:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s cultivate the trust \Nin him by praying specifically \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.07,0:07:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,about the things that we need help with.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.61,0:07:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But what if we pray constantly \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.74,0:07:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and we’re enduring a situation \Nand the problem persists? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.68,0:07:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What then? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.68,0:07:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice Luke 11:9, please. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.55,0:07:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus’ words give us \Nevery reason for confidence \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.56,0:07:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,when it says at Luke 11:9: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.79,0:08:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“So I say to you, keep on asking, \Nand it will be given you; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.20,0:08:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“keep on seeking, \Nand you will find; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.30,0:08:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,keep on knocking, \Nand it will be opened to you.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.14,0:08:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we want to do \Nwhatever is in our power \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.67,0:08:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to solve our problems, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.71,0:08:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,having confidence that in time Jehovah \Nwill give us the solution \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.25,0:08:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and until then he’ll help us endure.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.85,0:08:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember what happens to a mountain \Nwhen it’s put next to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.85,0:08:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It becomes a molehill. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.19,0:08:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to turn mountains into molehills \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.83,0:08:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,by throwing our concerns \Nupon Jehovah in prayer. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.36,0:08:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Micah’s confidence was not misplaced. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.17,0:08:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Soon he’ll be back with us \Nin the resurrection \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.40,0:08:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to witness the fulfillment of all \Nof Jehovah’s promises \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.34,0:08:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that he patiently waited for. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.44,0:08:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So, like him, may we curb \Nour natural feelings of impatience \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.08,0:08:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,by keeping wide awake in faith, \Nalways “on the lookout for Jehovah.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.12,0:00:04.02,Default2,,0,0,0,,今日の聖句と注解は—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.02,0:00:06.92,Default2,,0,0,0,,「待つ態度をどのように\N 保てますか」という—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.92,0:00:09.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,ものみの塔の研究記事から\N取られています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.93,0:00:14.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,なぜ今この点を考えるのか \N記事にはこうあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.03,0:00:17.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,“辛抱できずにいら立つのは危険です”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.77,0:00:21.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“性急に行動してしまう\N 可能性があるからです”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.91,0:00:25.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうしたら ずっと\N待っていられますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.08,0:00:29.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,どうぞミカ 7章7節をお開きください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.98,0:00:32.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,これは研究記事の主題聖句です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.35,0:00:36.22,Default2,,0,0,0,,ミカ 7章7節を一緒に読み—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.22,0:00:40.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,待つ態度を保つ上で ミカの良い手本が\N助けになることについて—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.42,0:00:42.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,少しの間考えましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.89,0:00:46.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,こうあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.00,0:00:49.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,“しかしわたしは \N 終始エホバに目を向ける”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.40,0:00:52.67,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしの救いの神を待ち望もう”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.67,0:00:58.88,Default2,,0,0,0,, 改訂版の脚注の考えを含めると \N“わたしの救いの神を辛抱強く待とう”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.88,0:01:01.75,Default2,,0,0,0,,“わたしの神は聞いてくださる”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.75,0:01:03.91,Default2,,0,0,0,,心に残る聖句です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.91,0:01:06.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,このたった1節の中でミカは—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.42,0:01:11.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分の そしてわたしたちの神\Nエホバについて3度述べています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.42,0:01:13.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして次のことが分かります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.86,0:01:18.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,もう望みはない 限界だ \Nそう感じる状況に置かれるとき—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.63,0:01:21.93,Default2,,0,0,0,,問題をエホバにゆだねると\Nどうなりますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.93,0:01:24.17,Default2,,0,0,0,,小さく見えるようになります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.17,0:01:28.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの助けで \N扱いやすいものになるのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.30,0:01:32.08,Default2,,0,0,0,,カール･クライン兄弟は\Nライフ･ストーリーでこう語りました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.08,0:01:35.18,Default2,,0,0,0,,“それが生じることを\N 神が許しておられるなら—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.18,0:01:38.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,“それに耐えることができる”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.41,0:01:42.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの助けがあれば \Nどんな試練や状況のもとでも—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.35,0:01:46.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,喜びを失わず\N踏みとどまることができるのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.39,0:01:51.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,ミカも そう確信していました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.76,0:01:54.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,もう一度7章7節をご覧ください\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.96,0:01:59.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,ミカは “終始エホバに\N目を向ける”と述べています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.40,0:02:05.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,つまり 自分は物見の塔の上にいる\N見張り番のようになる と言っていたのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.71,0:02:08.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,情景を描いてみましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.98,0:02:13.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,見張り番がしっかりと目を開けて \N辺りを注意深く見張っています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.28,0:02:17.52,Default2,,0,0,0,,ミカは霊的な意味でそう言いました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.52,0:02:18.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,待ち切れなくなったり—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.96,0:02:23.86,Default2,,0,0,0,,自分ではどうにもならないこと\Nについて考えていら立ったりはしない— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.86,0:02:25.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ミカはそう決意していました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.36,0:02:29.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし 待つ態度を保つのは\N簡単でしたか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.70,0:02:32.24,Default2,,0,0,0,,おそらくそうではなかったでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.24,0:02:37.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,文脈を見ると 当時のイスラエルと\Nユダの状況が分かります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.04,0:02:43.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,ミカ 7章2節以降で \N幾つかの点に注目しましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.55,0:02:46.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,“忠節な者は地からうせ”た\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.35,0:02:50.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,3節では “その手は悪事の上にある”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.05,0:02:54.59,Default2,,0,0,0,,4節には “彼らの最も善良な者は\Nおどろに似ており—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.59,0:02:59.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,“最も廉直な者もいばらの垣根に\N 勝らない”とあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.53,0:03:03.30,Default2,,0,0,0,,実際ミカは5節で \N“仲間を信じてはいけない”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.30,0:03:05.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,“腹心の友をも信頼してはいけない”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.90,0:03:10.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“あなたの懐に寝る女に対して\N 口を開くことにも用心せよ”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.04,0:03:16.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,6節では “息子は父を軽んじ \N娘はその母に逆らい—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.45,0:03:19.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,“嫁はそのしゅうとめに\N 逆らっているからである”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.38,0:03:23.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“人の敵はその家の者たち\N となっている”と言っています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.32,0:03:27.49,Default2,,0,0,0,,ミカは難しい時代に生きていました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.49,0:03:29.76,Default2,,0,0,0,,邪悪なアハズ王の時代—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.76,0:03:34.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,イスラエルは霊的にも道徳的にも\N堕落し悲惨な状態でした\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.87,0:03:39.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ミカの置かれていた状況は\Nあなたとも関係がありますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.37,0:03:44.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの民は皆 忍耐や辛抱を試されます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.41,0:03:47.48,Default2,,0,0,0,,利己的な世で暮らしているからです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.48,0:03:52.05,Default2,,0,0,0,,聖書によると 人々は\N“感謝”しない “忠節”でない—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.05,0:03:55.25,Default2,,0,0,0,,“自然の情愛”を持たない者になります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.25,0:04:00.06,Default2,,0,0,0,,イエスの予告通り 真のクリスチャンは\N“憎しみの的”です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.06,0:04:06.16,Default2,,0,0,0,,学校や職場で ほぼ毎日 憎まれ\N反対されている兄弟姉妹がいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.16,0:04:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,時には家族の中で 真理にいない\N家族から憎まれることもあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.60,0:04:16.41,Default2,,0,0,0,,憎しみを受け 投獄されている\N兄弟姉妹たちもいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.41,0:04:20.98,Default2,,0,0,0,,アゼルバイジャンの2人の姉妹について\N考えずにはいられません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.98,0:04:26.55,Default2,,0,0,0,,不当な迫害を受けている姉妹たちのため\Nわたしたちは熱烈に祈っています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.55,0:04:32.82,Default2,,0,0,0,,また エリトリア ナゴルノ･カラバフ \Nシンガポール 韓国 トルクメニスタンの—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.82,0:04:35.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,600人以上の兄弟たちのことも考えます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.13,0:04:40.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,わたしたちは 不公正が\N正されることを待ち望んでいます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.36,0:04:44.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,状況が変化するよう心から願っています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.33,0:04:47.77,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 辛抱できずいら立つでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.77,0:04:50.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,いいえ 待ち続けます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.11,0:04:56.38,Default2,,0,0,0,,加えて 多くの兄弟姉妹は\N健康の問題に直面しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.38,0:05:00.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,これも 辛抱や忍耐を試みられる状況です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.42,0:05:03.72,Default2,,0,0,0,,あなた自身 あるいは\N家族や友人のだれかが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.72,0:05:08.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,程度は様々でも こうした問題と\N闘っているかもしれません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.66,0:05:14.40,Default2,,0,0,0,,今月のBroadcastingで パナマの\Nサビナ･エルナンデス姉妹が登場しました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.40,0:05:18.57,Default2,,0,0,0,,姉妹には 生まれながらに\N重い障害があります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.57,0:05:22.61,Default2,,0,0,0,,生まれた時から \N普通の生活ができていません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.61,0:05:26.88,Default2,,0,0,0,,でも 姉妹の手本は本当に励みになります！\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.88,0:05:30.85,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを信頼し \N待つ態度を身に着けてきました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.85,0:05:35.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,健康の問題があっても \Nベストを尽くしてエホバに奉仕しています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.69,0:05:39.62,Default2,,0,0,0,,すべての問題がなくなる時を\N心待ちにしています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.62,0:05:43.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,本当にその時が来てほしいですね\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.06,0:05:47.90,Default2,,0,0,0,,間もなく すべての問題がなくなります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.90,0:05:50.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,思ったより早くその時が来るでしょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.43,0:05:56.11,Default2,,0,0,0,,しかし それがもうすぐだとしても \Nもう少し後だとしても—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.11,0:06:00.54,Default2,,0,0,0,,ミカの手本から何か学べるでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.54,0:06:03.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,もう少し考えましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.45,0:06:06.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,ミカは およそ60年忠実に奉仕し—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.68,0:06:11.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバの裁きに関するメッセージが\Nその通りに実現するのを目にしました\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.09,0:06:16.23,Default2,,0,0,0,,預言者としての活動の成果を見たのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.23,0:06:20.33,Default2,,0,0,0,,ではミカは 約束すべてが\N実現するのを見ましたか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.33,0:06:21.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,いいえ\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.63,0:06:24.97,Default2,,0,0,0,,では 辛抱して待ち 活動し続け—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.97,0:06:27.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを信頼していられた\Nのはなぜですか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.24,0:06:33.84,Default2,,0,0,0,,いずれエホバが約束通り必ず行動される\Nと確信していたからです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.84,0:06:36.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,エホバを信頼し切っていたのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.01,0:06:43.35,Default2,,0,0,0,,では ミカと同じような信頼 確信をもって\N待つ態度を培うため 何ができますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.35,0:06:46.66,Default2,,0,0,0,,さらにできることがあるでしょうか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.66,0:06:49.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,2つ 思い起こしてみましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.26,0:06:53.63,Default2,,0,0,0,,1つが テサロニケ第一 5章17節にあります\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.63,0:06:55.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,読んでみましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.26,0:06:59.07,Default2,,0,0,0,,テサロニケ第一 5章17節です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.07,0:07:01.37,Default2,,0,0,0,,暗記しているかもしれません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.37,0:07:04.01,Default2,,0,0,0,,英語では簡単な2つの言葉です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.01,0:07:06.28,Default2,,0,0,0,,何ができますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.28,0:07:09.65,Default2,,0,0,0,,“絶えず祈りなさい”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.65,0:07:12.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,祈りはエホバとのコミュニケーションです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.32,0:07:16.69,Default2,,0,0,0,,話し過ぎと注意されることは\N決してありません\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.69,0:07:20.96,Default2,,0,0,0,,ものみの塔はこの聖句を引用し\Nこう述べています\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.96,0:07:25.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,“ご意志を行なう人がささげる祈りに\N 制限を設けてはおらず—”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.56,0:07:28.36,Default2,,0,0,0,,“快く聴いてくださるのです”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.36,0:07:31.10,Default2,,0,0,0,,では エホバの勧めに応じましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.10,0:07:33.50,Default2,,0,0,0,,苦しんでいることについて絶えず祈り—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.50,0:07:38.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,助けが必要なことについて\N具体的に祈り 信頼を保ちましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.08,0:07:42.45,Default2,,0,0,0,,では いつも祈りながら\N踏みとどまってきましたが—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.45,0:07:45.68,Default2,,0,0,0,,問題がまだなくならない場合は\Nどうですか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.68,0:07:51.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,ルカ 11章9節のイエスの言葉は\N本当に確信を強めてくれます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.42,0:07:55.89,Default2,,0,0,0,,“それゆえにわたしはあなた方に言います”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.89,0:07:59.56,Default2,,0,0,0,,“求めつづけなさい\N そうすれば与えられます”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.56,0:08:03.53,Default2,,0,0,0,,“探しつづけなさい\N そうすれば見いだせます”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.53,0:08:07.00,Default2,,0,0,0,,“たたきつづけなさい\N そうすれば開かれます”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.17,0:08:11.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,問題を解決するため できることをします\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.21,0:08:14.21,Default2,,0,0,0,,そして いずれエホバが解決してくださる—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.21,0:08:19.95,Default2,,0,0,0,,その時まで立っていられるよう\N助けてくださる と信じ続けるのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.95,0:08:24.32,Default2,,0,0,0,,山のような問題は\Nエホバのそばに来るとどうなりますか？\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.32,0:08:26.42,Default2,,0,0,0,,小さなもぐら塚です\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.42,0:08:33.13,Default2,,0,0,0,,では祈って 心配をエホバに渡して\N山を小さな塚にしましょう\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.13,0:08:35.43,Default2,,0,0,0,,ミカの確信は報われます\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.43,0:08:40.70,Default2,,0,0,0,,復活し 辛抱して待ってきた\Nエホバの約束が実現するのを見るのです\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.70,0:08:44.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,では ミカのように\N信仰を保って見張り続け—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.51,0:08:47.51,Default2,,0,0,0,,待ち切れなくなる\N自然な気持ちを乗り越え—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.51,0:08:49.26,Default2,,0,0,0,,いつも“エホバに目を向け”て\Nいることができますように\N
